        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/140/1",
        "text": [
          " : «إِذَا اِشْتَرَى اَلرَّجُلُ هَدْيَهُ وَ قَمَطَهُ فِي بَيْتِهِ فَقَدْ بَلَغَ مَحِلَّهُ فَإِنْ شَاءَ فَلْيَحْلِقْ »."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.3089 - Ali ibn Abi Hamzah narrated from Abu Abdullah (as), who said:\n\"If a man purchases his hady (sacrificial animal) and confines it in his house, it has reached its designated place. If he wishes, he may shave his head.\""
          ]
        }
      }
